The paper discusses the use of deep learning (specifically, the AlexNet architecture) to automatically classify images as diagnostic or non-diagnostic in the context of brain tumor surgery. This involves image analysis and computer vision, which are typically associated with the computer science sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of deep learning suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a 4-fold cross validation method, which is commonly used in neural network training and evaluation, suggesting a focus on neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the potential clinical applications of the proposed method, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
